'''纺锤体神经元'''（英文：Spindle neuron），又称'''冯·艾克诺默神经元'''（Von Economo neuron），是一种有着纺锤形状[[细胞体|细胞体]]的[[神经元|神经元]]，位于某些[[哺乳动物|哺乳动物]]的[[大脑皮层|大脑皮层]]（第5层）<ref name=":0">{{Cite journal|title=Von Economo neurons: Clinical and evolutionary perspectives|url=https://www.sciencedirect.com/science/article/pii/S0010945211002784|last=Butti|first=Camilla|last2=Santos|first2=Micaela|date=2013-01-01|journal=Cortex|issue=1|doi=10.1016/j.cortex.2011.10.004|volume=49|pages=312–326|language=en|issn=0010-9452|last3=Uppal|first3=Neha|last4=Hof|first4=Patrick R.|access-date=2021-04-04|archive-date=2013-01-17|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20130117081921/http://www.sciencedirect.com/science/article/pii/S0010945211002784|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref name=":1">{{Cite journal|title=Transcriptomic evidence that von Economo neurons are regionally specialized extratelencephalic-projecting excitatory neurons|url=https://www.nature.com/articles/s41467-020-14952-3|last=Hodge|first=Rebecca D.|last2=Miller|first2=Jeremy A.|date=2020-03-03|journal=Nature Communications|issue=1|doi=10.1038/s41467-020-14952-3|volume=11|pages=1172|language=en|issn=2041-1723|last3=Novotny|first3=Mark|last4=Kalmbach|first4=Brian E.|last5=Ting|first5=Jonathan T.|last6=Bakken|first6=Trygve E.|last7=Aevermann|first7=Brian D.|last8=Barkan|first8=Eliza R.|last9=Berkowitz-Cerasano|first9=Madeline L.|access-date=2021-04-04|archive-date=2021-11-28|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20211128081447/https://www.nature.com/articles/s41467-020-14952-3|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref>{{Cite journal|title=The von Economo neurons in frontoinsular and anterior cingulate cortex in great apes and humans|url=https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/20512377/|last=Allman|first=John M.|last2=Tetreault|first2=Nicole A.|date=2010-06|journal=Brain Structure & Function|issue=5-6|doi=10.1007/s00429-010-0254-0|volume=214|pages=495–517|issn=1863-2661|pmid=20512377|last3=Hakeem|first3=Atiya Y.|last4=Manaye|first4=Kebreten F.|last5=Semendeferi|first5=Katerina|last6=Erwin|first6=Joseph M.|last7=Park|first7=Soyoung|last8=Goubert|first8=Virginie|last9=Hof|first9=Patrick R.|access-date=2021-04-04|archive-date=2022-01-20|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220120225156/https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/20512377/|dead-url=no}}</ref>。在[[人腦|人脑]]中，纺锤体神经元位于[[前扣带皮层|前扣带皮层]]、前[[岛叶|岛叶]]皮层<ref name=":0" /><ref name=":1" />。 纺锤体神经元属于[[雙極神經元|双极神经元]]，纺锤顶上有一个[[轴突|轴突]]，并且在反方向只有一个[[树突|树突]]<ref name=":1" />。其命名是纪念发现者、[[奥地利|奥地利]]神经学家[[康斯坦丁·冯·艾克诺默|康斯坦丁·冯·艾克诺默]]<ref>{{Cite journal|title=Constantin von Economo (1876–1931) and his legacy to neuroscience|url=https://doi.org/10.1007/s00381-015-2647-0|last=Kaya|first=Yasemin|last2=Uysal|first2=Hilmi|date=2016-02-01|journal=Child's Nervous System|issue=2|doi=10.1007/s00381-015-2647-0|volume=32|pages=217–220|language=en|issn=1433-0350|last3=Akkoyunlu|first3=Gokhan|last4=Sarikcioglu|first4=Levent}}</ref>。

纺锤体神经元是体型较大的细胞，被认为可能是一些脑部较大物种（[[人科|人科]]、[[大象|大象]]以及[[鯨豚類|鲸豚类]]物种）能够进行快速交流的基础，从而形成“[[社交|社交]]”<ref>{{Cite web|title=Brain Cells for Socializing|url=https://www.smithsonianmag.com/science-nature/brain-cells-for-socializing-133855450/|accessdate=2021-04-04|work=Smithsonian Magazine|language=en|archive-date=2021-03-23|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210323161204/https://www.smithsonianmag.com/science-nature/brain-cells-for-socializing-133855450/|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|title=Spindle Neuron - an overview|url=https://www.sciencedirect.com/topics/veterinary-science-and-veterinary-medicine/spindle-neuron|accessdate=2021-04-04|work=|publisher=Science Direct|language=en|archive-date=2017-11-08|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20171108053816/http://www.sciencedirect.com/topics/veterinary-science-and-veterinary-medicine/spindle-neuron|dead-url=no}}</ref>。纺锤体神经元受损可能导致社交障碍以及情感功能障碍<ref name=":0" />。

